{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.applyWith\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">applyWith</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`apply e` tries to match the current goal against the conclusion of `e`'s type.\nIf it succeeds, then the tactic returns as many subgoals as the number of premises that\nhave not been fixed by type inference or type class resolution.\nNon-dependent premises are added before dependent ones.\n\nThe `apply` tactic uses higher-order pattern matching, type class resolution,\nand first-order unification with dependent types.\n\n\nExtensions:\n\n * * `apply (config := cfg) e` allows for additional configuration (see `Lean.Meta.ApplyConfig`):\n     * `newGoals` controls which new goals are added by `apply`, in which order.\n     * `-synthAssignedInstances` will not synthesize instance implicit arguments if they have been\n       assigned by `isDefEq`.\n     * `+allowSynthFailures` will create new goals when instance synthesis fails, rather than erroring.\n     * `+approx` enables `isDefEq` approximations (see `Lean.Meta.approxDefEq`).","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.applyWith","kind":"def","line":67,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.applyWith","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.lean#L67-L71"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.elabApplyConfig\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">elabApplyConfig</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Lean.Syntax</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Tactic/Basic.html#Lean.Elab.Tactic.TacticM\">Lean.Elab.Tactic.TacticM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Meta.ApplyConfig\">Lean.Meta.ApplyConfig</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Elaborator for the configuration in `apply (config := cfg)` syntax. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.elabApplyConfig","kind":"def","line":54,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.elabApplyConfig","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.lean#L54-L55"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.optConfigOf\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">optConfigOf</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Lean.Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntax\">Lean.TSyntax</a> <span class=\"fn\">`Lean.Parser.Tactic.optConfig</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Convert `manyConfig`, `optConfig` or `config` syntax into `optConfig`,\nfor use in a `declare_config_elab` elaborator. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.optConfigOf","kind":"def","line":49,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.optConfigOf","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.lean#L49-L52"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.getManyConfigItems\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">getManyConfigItems</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Lean.Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TSyntaxArray\">Lean.TSyntaxArray</a> <span class=\"fn\">`Lean.Parser.Tactic.configItem</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Extracts the items from a tactic configuration,\neither a `Mathlib.Tactic.manyConfig`, `Lean.Parser.Tactic.optConfig`, `Lean.Parser.Tactic.config`,\nor these wrapped in null nodes.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.getManyConfigItems","kind":"def","line":34,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.getManyConfigItems","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.lean#L34-L47"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.manyConfig\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">manyConfig</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"At least one configuration option for tactics.\n\nIf a configuration elaborator is defined as `declare_config_elab elabMyConfig MyConfigStruct`,\na `manyConfig` syntax item ```cfg : TSyntax ``manyConfig``` can be passed to it using\n`elabMyConfig (optConfigOf cfg)`.\n\n`optConfig` allows zero or more options, `manyConfig` requires at least one option.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.html#Mathlib.Tactic.manyConfig","kind":"def","line":24,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.manyConfig","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/ApplyWith.lean#L24-L32"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Init","Lean.Elab.Eval","Lean.Elab.Tactic.ElabTerm","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Config"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.ApplyWith"}